  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Can I take GABA with melatonin?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes. GABA and melatonin work through different mechanisms and are complementary for sleep. Melatonin regulates the circadian rhythm — it signals to the brain that it is time for sleep, helping with sleep onset (falling asleep). GABA reduces neuronal excitability — it calms racing thoughts and anxiety that prevent sleep, addressing the "can\'t turn off my brain" problem. Together, melatonin handles the timing of sleep while GABA addresses the mental quiet needed for sleep. Many sleep gummies combine both ingredients. Start with low doses of each (0.5-1mg melatonin + 100-200mg GABA) before increasing.' } },
  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Are GABA gummies safe?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'GABA supplements are considered safe for most healthy adults at recommended doses (100-750mg). Side effects are uncommon but may include mild tingling or flushing at higher doses (this is harmless and temporary). GABA should not be combined with prescription sedatives, benzodiazepines, or barbiturates, as it may enhance their sedative effects. People with depression should consult their healthcare provider, as GABA can affect mood-related neurotransmitter balance. Pregnant and breastfeeding women should avoid GABA supplements due to limited safety data. Do not operate machinery or drive after taking GABA if it causes significant drowsiness.' } },
